20 June 2012The Inter-Ministerial Committee on the Gauteng Freeway Improvement Project (GFIP), which is chaired by Deputy President Kgalema Motlanthe, will meet with Opposition to Urban Tolling Alliance (OUTA) as part of stakeholder consultations on the GFIP. Media are invited to a photo opportunity scheduled to take place just before the start of the meeting. The meeting details are: Date: 21 June 2012 Time: 11h00 Venue: Room 159, Union Building, Pretoria At the end of the meeting, a joint media statement by both government and OUTA will be issued. Very Important: Media wishing to attend must please RSVP to Pheliswa Sebati on 082 413 4609 email: Pheliswa@gcis.gov.za or Terrence Manase on 0823386707 email: Terrence@po.gov.za Enquiries: Thabo Masebe 082 410 8087 Issued by Government Communication and Information System (GCIS)